snippet.title: Comic Doug Stanhope To Amber Heard: Your lawsuit is 'bullshit'
snippet.description:
Stanhope insists her legal action is "bullshit" because he was merely defending his friend in a post on his website - not penning a explosive op-ed for TheWrap, in which he claimed the actress was blackmailing her estranged husband.

Appearing on The Howard Stern Show on Monday (20Jun16), the 49-year-old said he put his thoughts down in a post on his website six days after Depp and Heard officially split last month (May16).

He told Stern, "The title was 'At a Loss for Words...' TheWrap got it as an exclusive, however that worked, and said, 'Amber Heard Is Blackmailing Johnny Depp - This Is How I Know'. I didn't write that f**king title. I didn't put that stupid tabloid title in there. I'm a better writer than that, so I don't know if it's hinged on that, I don't know how much of it is spite."

Heard has called the piece "highly defamatory", but Stanhope insists his pal Depp was happy with it: "I had no contact with him (Depp) until he texted me after that went out and said, 'Hey, thanks for being honest'. He didn't know that was going out. I was a little petrified because it kind of made him look like a b**ch."

And Stanhope isn't taking Amber's legal attack too seriously, smiling, "The idea of some Hollywood supermodel lady winning all of my s**t... She would be locking the doors driving down my street even without seeing a person. I live on the Mexican border in this dirty pothole-riddled neighbourhood."

The comic reveals his pal Depp gave him a heads up about the split and suggested Amber might accuse the actor of abusing her when the two friends spent time together on 21 May (16).

Stanhope told Stern, "He was alluding to the fact that she was going to do something like this. She didn't come out until a week later that that happened. But it happened that night, and he was alluding to she's going to do something like this.

"I think what she's trying to do is make me shut the f**k up, because I can't say anything about it, and now I'm talking more."

Heard, 30, filed her defamation lawsuit against Stanhope on 3 June (16). Her lawyers accused him of trying to "divert public attention away from the true facts regarding Depp which caused their marriage to fail, namely, that Depp repeatedly abused Heard throughout their marriage, at times to the point of her fearing for her life."

Audio Courtesy of "The Howard Stern Show"
snippet.localized.title: Comic Doug Stanhope To Amber Heard: Your lawsuit is 'bullshit'
snippet.localized.description:
Stanhope insists her legal action is "bullshit" because he was merely defending his friend in a post on his website - not penning a explosive op-ed for TheWrap, in which he claimed the actress was blackmailing her estranged husband.

Appearing on The Howard Stern Show on Monday (20Jun16), the 49-year-old said he put his thoughts down in a post on his website six days after Depp and Heard officially split last month (May16).

He told Stern, "The title was 'At a Loss for Words...' TheWrap got it as an exclusive, however that worked, and said, 'Amber Heard Is Blackmailing Johnny Depp - This Is How I Know'. I didn't write that f**king title. I didn't put that stupid tabloid title in there. I'm a better writer than that, so I don't know if it's hinged on that, I don't know how much of it is spite."

Heard has called the piece "highly defamatory", but Stanhope insists his pal Depp was happy with it: "I had no contact with him (Depp) until he texted me after that went out and said, 'Hey, thanks for being honest'. He didn't know that was going out. I was a little petrified because it kind of made him look like a b**ch."

And Stanhope isn't taking Amber's legal attack too seriously, smiling, "The idea of some Hollywood supermodel lady winning all of my s**t... She would be locking the doors driving down my street even without seeing a person. I live on the Mexican border in this dirty pothole-riddled neighbourhood."

The comic reveals his pal Depp gave him a heads up about the split and suggested Amber might accuse the actor of abusing her when the two friends spent time together on 21 May (16).

Stanhope told Stern, "He was alluding to the fact that she was going to do something like this. She didn't come out until a week later that that happened. But it happened that night, and he was alluding to she's going to do something like this.

"I think what she's trying to do is make me shut the f**k up, because I can't say anything about it, and now I'm talking more."

Heard, 30, filed her defamation lawsuit against Stanhope on 3 June (16). Her lawyers accused him of trying to "divert public attention away from the true facts regarding Depp which caused their marriage to fail, namely, that Depp repeatedly abused Heard throughout their marriage, at times to the point of her fearing for her life."

Audio Courtesy of "The Howard Stern Show"

snippet.title: Amber Heard says meeting Syria refugees left a mark on her soul
snippet.description:
(5 Apr 2018) Actress Amber Heard said Thursday (5 APRIL 2018) that encounters with Syrian refugees and foreign medical volunteers helping the displaced have left an "an indelible mark" on her soul.
Heard, 31, spent a week in Jordan as part of a delegation of the Syrian American Medical Society (SAMS), visiting the kingdom's largest camp for Syrian refugees and rehabilitation centers for those wounded in Syria's seven-year-old civil war.
In an interview, Heard said she knew little about the conflict before the trip, but that she had become friendly with a family of Syrian immigrants to the United States. During a recent holiday dinner, she said she raised a glass and toasted "my big, extended Syrian family for adopting the American, and that's how I feel."
Heard said SAMS, a global medical relief organization, approached her to join a 53-member medical mission to Jordan, home to about 660,000 of some 5.5 million Syrian refugees. Most of the displaced Syrians have settled in overburdened regional host countries, struggling to survive on menial jobs, food vouchers and small cash stipends from aid groups.
Over the past week, the medical mission visited Zaatari, Jordan's largest camp for Syrian refugees, as well as rehabilitation centers for the wounded.
"My biggest takeaway from this trip is the indelible mark left on my soul after spending a week on the ground here," Heard told The Associated Press in the Jordanian capital of Amman.
Heard said she was moved by "the resilience and the spirit of everyone involved" and being reminded of the "beautiful side of human nature."
Medical volunteers treated more than 4,300 patients in three locations in Jordan during the mission and also trained visiting Syrian doctors, SAMS said.
Heard appears in the upcoming superhero film "Aquaman," playing a warrior in the undersea nation of Atlantis.
The actress said that Hollywood still "has a long way to go" when it comes to gender pay equality and representation of women and minorities.
"Hollywood needs to catch up and catch up fast," she said, noting that women still have far fewer speaking roles than men and earn far less, on average.
Heard, who went through a contentious divorce from actor Johnny Depp in 2016, also weighed in on the #MeToo movement, saying it's up against a "longstanding status quo of powerful men silencing women."

snippet.title: Aishwarya Rai Bachchan rules the runway at Paris Fashion Week; looks divine in white
snippet.description:
Aishwarya Rai Bachchan¬†was a vision in white at the¬†Paris Fashion Week.

The former Miss World had all eyes on her when she strutted down the ramp in an all-white tradition-meets-modern ensemble. The actress wore her hair down in loose waves and added a pop of colour with her pink lip colour.

Photos and videos from the show sent fans on social media into a tizzy. Many were blown away by the actress' flawless walk down the ramp as she twirled and used her pleated dupatta as her best accessory.
Ash walked the ramp along with a host of Hollywood stars like¬†Helen Mirren, Amber Heard, as well as father-daughter duo, Nikolaj Coster-Waldau and Fillippa Coster-Waldau.

Other celebs on the runway included Leyna Bloom, Aja Naomi King, Kat Graham,¬†Soo Joo Park, Baptiste Giabiconi, and Isabeli Fontana.

Also seen joining the lineup were¬†Camila Cabello¬†and Katherine Langford.

According to reports, Helen, Amber, Aja, Aishwarya, Camila and Katherine walked the ramp as brand ambassadors for a beauty line.

On the professional front, Aishwarya will make her come back to the big screen with¬†Mani Ratnam's 'Ponniyin Selvan'. The period drama is slated to hit the silver screens in 2022.

If you haven‚Äôt been living under a rock, you‚Äôve probably heard all about the Johnny Depp and Amber Heard fiasco somewhere on the internet. It‚Äôs one narrative that has its twists and turns especially regarding the accusations the couple has made against each other. 
But to keep you refreshed, the pair have been dating for quite a while before eventually getting hitched together in a Los Angeles private ceremony in 2015. However, one year later, multiple sources have reported that Amber has officially filed for divorce from Johnny alongside a temporary restraining order on the grounds of physical abuse. She said that at the time of the divorce an incident took place wherein Johnny had lost control and threw his phone at her eventually leaving Amber bruised in her face. However, an insider had told People magazine that there were no investigations or proof that such a crime had taken place.
And while they have been officially separated since 2017, Heard took it to The Washington Post in 2018 to write an op-ed for speaking out about women and domestic abuse and Johnny did not take it lightly. 
‚ÄúI became a public figure representing domestic abuse, and I felt the full force of our culture‚Äôs wrath for women who speak out,‚Äù she wrote in the article.

‚ÄúThe op-ed depended on the central premise that Ms. Heard was a domestic abuse victim and that Mr. Depp perpetrated domestic violence against her,‚Äù Johnny‚Äôs lawyers said.
In 2020, phone recordings of Amber blatantly admitting to having hit Johnny on multiple occasions.
‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know what the motion of my actual hand was, but you‚Äôre fine, I did not hurt you, I did not punch you, I was hitting you,‚Äù she said in the phone call.
And as mentioned, the whole situation has been quite damaging for their careers as Johnny announced on Instagram in November 2020 that he has been asked to resign from his role as Grindelwald in the third ‚ÄúFantastic Beasts‚Äù film ‚Äì a role he had successfully been playing since 2017.

snippet.title: Celebrities With The Most Scientifically Beautiful Faces

There‚Äôs actually a science behind why A-list celebrities are much more attractive than an average person. It may not have anything to do with makeup, facials, or hair extensions. In fact, it actually has more to do to with research and science. The more beautiful a celebrity is, the more likely they are to land large roles, and the more likely we are to enjoy seeing their faces in magazines and on screens.

Scientific research has proven that having a perfectly proportioned and balanced face can propel a celebrity‚Äôs career; people are more drawn to symmetry. Take a look at our roundup of celebrities who have the most scientifically beautiful faces in Hollywood.

snippet.title: Camila Cabello, Amber Heard, and Dame Helen Mirren headline L'Oreal at Paris Fashion Week
snippet.description:
#CamilaCabello #AmberHeard #L'Oreal
Camila Cabello, Amber Heard, and Dame Helen Mirren headline L'Oreal at Paris Fashion Week. That's quite an Eiffel! Camila Cabello, Amber Heard and Dame Helen Mirren lead the Paris Fashion Week glamour as they walk the L'Oreal catwalk at the foot of the iconic French landmark. 
Camila Cabello, Amber Heard and Dame Helen Mirren led the catwalk glamour on Sunday afternoon as L'Oreal kicked off their latest show at Paris Fashion Week. 

The French cosmetics brand drafted in their three celebrity ambassadors for a typically offbeat presentation at the foot of the iconic Eiffel Tower. 

Accompanied by an assortment of models and dancers, the three stars were on hand to help L'Oreal unveil their spring-summer 2022 range at the biannual event.

snippet.title: "That's Enough!" Judge Loses It After Amber Heard Asks For Case Dismissal!
snippet.description:
The Judge Loses His Temper Silencing Amber Heard After She Asks For A Case Dismissal For The Third Time!

‚úÖ Subscribe & HIT that notification bell for more Celebrity Content!

"‚ÄúAmber is not a product of domestic maltreatment, she is a perpetrator‚Äù, says the suit that her ex-husband Johny Depp filed against her.

snippet.title: JONNY DEPP VS. AMBER HEARD: Alkohol, Eifersucht und vielleicht Haue - Rosenkrieg der besonderen Art
snippet.description:
Eifersucht, ja - Schl√§ge aus Eifersucht, nein. Schauspieler Johnny Depp hat vor Gericht am Mittwoch zur√ºckgewiesen, seine Ex-Frau Amber Heard geschlagen zu haben. Zwar habe er eifers√ºchtig sein k√∂nnen, r√§umte er bei einem Kreuzverh√∂r der Anw√§ltin Sasha Wass in London ein. Aber das habe nie dazu gef√ºhrt, dass er gewaltt√§tig geworden sei.

In dem Verfahren geht es darum, dass die britische Boulevardzeitung ¬´The Sun¬ª Depp 2018 in einem Artikel als ¬´Ehefrauen-Schl√§ger¬ª bezeichnet hatte. Depp hat den Verleger der ¬´Sun¬ª, News Group Newspapers, deshalb wegen Verleumdung verklagt. Heard nimmt an dem dreiw√∂chigen Verfahren teil und es wird erwartet, dass auch sie sp√§ter aussagen wird. Der Fall hat sich zu einem bitteren Rosenkrieg zwischen den beiden entwickelt. Sie werfen sich gegenseitig Gewalt, Kontrollsucht und Hinterlist vor.

Zum¬†Prozessauftakt am Dienstag hatte Depp bereits gesagt, er habe seine Ex-Frau nicht misshandelt. Ihre Behauptungen seien ¬´krank¬ª und ¬´total unwahr¬ª.

Am Mittwoch erz√§hlte die ¬´Sun¬ª-Anw√§ltin Wass Schilderungen von Heard nach, die sich im M√§rz 2013 abgespielt haben sollen. Danach wurde Depp w√ºtend wegen eines Gem√§ldes, das in Heards Schlafzimmer hing und von deren fr√ºherer Partnerin stammte, der K√ºnstlerin Tasya Van Ree. Er habe das Bild von der Wand genommen, versucht, es in Brand zu stecken und Heard geschlagen, als sie sich einmischte.

Depp wies ebenfalls zur√ºck, dass er Heard geschlagen habe, nachdem sie √ºber sein Tattoo ¬´Wino Forever¬ª gelacht habe. ¬´Ich erinnere mich nicht an einen Streit √ºber eines meiner Tattoos¬ª, sagte Depp. Er lie√ü es nach eigenen Angaben √§ndern. Jahre vorher hatte er sich von Winona Ryder getrennt, die urspr√ºngliche T√§towierung lautete ¬´Winona Forever¬ª.

Weitere Anschuldigungen, gewaltt√§tig gegen√ºber Heard gewesen zu sein, wies er mit Kommentaren wie ¬´nicht korrekt¬ª und ¬´schlicht und einfach unwahr¬ª zur√ºck. Als er √ºber einen mutma√ülichen Vorfall befragt wurde, bei dem er Heards Yorkshire Terrier Pistol aus einem Auto herausgehalten haben soll, sagte er, das sei absolut falsch. ¬´Das ist nicht meine Vorstellung von Spa√ü, auch wenn ich einen eher schr√§gen Sinn f√ºr Humor habe.¬ª

Wass las Depp einen Auszug aus einer E-Mail vor, die Heard ihm 2013 schrieb, aber nie abschickte. Darin beschrieb die Schauspielerin Depps Charakter wie ¬´Dr. Jekyll und Mr. Hyde¬ª; sein Verhalten komme einem ¬´Disco-Blutbad¬ª gleich. Der Hollywood-Star erkl√§rte dazu, die E-Mail sei ein Beweis daf√ºr, dass Heard ein ¬´Dossier¬ª aufgebaut habe, ¬´eine Versicherungspolice f√ºr sp√§ter¬ª.

Depp und die Anw√§ltin gerieten au√üerdem √ºber Heards Angabe aneinander, sie habe seinen Alkohol- und Drogenkonsum z√ºgeln wollen. Sie habe versucht, Depp trocken zu bekommen und niemals Kokain w√§hrend ihrer Beziehung genommen, sagte Heard demnach. ¬´Es gab viele Momente in unserer Beziehung, von Anfang an, wo sie das Kokain nicht nur mit einer Rasierklinge in Lines gezogen hat, sondern wo sie das Kokain auf ihre Finger genommen und auf ihr Zahnfleisch gerieben hat¬ª, sagte Depp dazu. Als Wass Heard mit den Worten zitierte, oft habe sie zwei oder drei Gl√§ser Wein am Abend getrunken, schoss der zur√ºck: ¬´Zwei oder drei Flaschen.¬ª ¬´Das ist kompletter Unsinn¬ª, entgegnete darauf die Anw√§ltin.

snippet.title: Camila Cabello, Amber Heard, Helen Mirren, Eva Longoria walk in L'Oreal show at Paris Fashion Week
snippet.description:
(28 Sep 2019) CABELLO, HEARD, MIRREN, LONGORIA WALK IN L'OREAL SHOW AT PARIS FASHION WEEK
Cabila Cabello, Amber Heard, Helen Mirren and Eva Longoria were among the stars walking the runway at L'Oreal Paris' third annual fashion show during Paris Fashion Week. 
The show dubbed "Le D√©fil√©" was held in the courtyard of the Monnaie de Paris on Saturday afternoon (28 SEPTEMBER 2019), featuring a diverse selection of models and spokespeople. 
Heard and Cabello, both brand ambassadors, made their first-ever appearances for the house. Longoria carried her baby son, Santiago, onto the runway for the grand finale. Mirren and Andie MacDowell proved that beauty knows no age. 
The 32-model lineup also included Doutzen Kroes, Soo Joo Park, and Aishwarya Rai. Stars such as Naomi Campbell and Olga Kurylenko watched from the front row, in the company of the brand's first-ever female president, Delphine Viguier-Hovasse.
Fashions were by emerging labels as well as renowned brands including Balmain, Dries Van Noten, Elie Saab, Karl Lagerfeld and more. A 40-musician orchestra accompanied the show.

snippet.title: DON'T LOOK UP  | Leonardo DiCaprio, Jennifer Lawrence, Ariana Grande | Netflix
snippet.description:
Don't Look Up is an upcoming American satirical science fiction black comedy film written, produced, and directed by Adam McKay. It stars Leonardo DiCaprio and Jennifer Lawrence as two low-level astronomers attempting, via a media tour, to warn mankind about an approaching comet that will destroy Earth. Rob Morgan, Jonah Hill, Mark Rylance, Tyler Perry, Ron Perlman, Timoth√©e Chalamet, Ariana Grande, Scott Mescudi, Cate Blanchett, and Meryl Streep round out the ensemble cast. The film is a satirical tackling of the climate change crisis. Ariana Grande and Kid Cudi also collaborated on the song "Just Look Up" for the soundtrack.

Produced by Hyperobject Industries and Bluegrass Films, the film is set to receive a limited theatrical release on December 10, 2021, prior to streaming on Netflix on December 24, 2021.

Johnny Depp Finally Reveals His Thoughts On Defeating Amber Heard In Court!

‚úÖ Subscribe & HIT that notification bell for more Celebrity Content!

It is true that Johnny Depp defeated Amber Heard? Johnny Depp and his ex-wife have had a legal battle for several years now, and that is that Amber accused him of domestic violence. But Johnny is more than determined to end this farce and expose his ex-wife in all this trouble. Will Johnny finally be able to get his life and career back after the whole truth comes out? And will Hollywood welcome him with open arms once this happens? After Johnny Depp lost his high-profile libel case against the publishers of The Sun newspaper over a 2018 article that described him as a "wife-beater," the actor announced that he has been "asked to resign" from the upcoming "Fantastic Beasts 3." Depp has vehemently denied the claims of abuse but was once again denied permission to appeal the court's ruling in March 2021.
